gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Suns 125, Timberwolves 106
gameRecap.excerpt: The Suns defeated the Timberwolves, 125-106. Bradley Beal led Phoenix with 36 points (6-6 3PT), six rebounds, and five assists as Devin Booker (23 points, seven assists) and Grayson Allen (20 points, six rebounds) totaled 43 points. Rudy Gobert led Minnesota in the loss with 21 points and seven rebounds. The Suns end the year at 49-33 while Minnesota ends at 56-26.
